This task is for adding the '__invoke' suggestion when declaring a function.

PHP 5.4 now supports treating objects as functions.
For example:
{code:php}
<?php
class MyClass{  
    function __invoke() {
        return print('hello!'); 
    }
}
$mine= new MyClass();
echo $mine(); // Outputs: 'hello!'
?>
{code}

PHP 5.4 supports calling method on object instantiation.
{code:php}
<?php
class MyClass{
    public $a = 1234;
 
    public function getValue() {
        return $this->a;
    }
    public function setValue($val) {
        $this->a = $val;
        return $this;
    }
}

// and you can also chain method calls
$mine = (new MyClass)->setValue(20)->getValue(); 
?>
{code}

Content assist for types that use other traits should include the functionality that was defined in the traits.
For example:
{code:php}
<?php
trait Base{
    public static function getInstance() { ... };
    public function printInfo() { ... };
}

class A {
    use Base;
}

class B extends OtherClass{
    use Base;
    // ...
}

// The trait method should be available for both types
A::getInstance();
B::getInstance();
// Also, instances of those types should provide the trait methods
$a = new A;
$a->printInfo();
?>
{code}

Add support for content assisting on a 'trait' use calls.
For example:
{code:php}
<?php
trait Base{
    public static function getInstance() { 
      // ...
    }
}

class A {
    use Base; // Content assist for "Base" should appear after the "use".
    // ...
}
?>
{code}

The traits suggestions should appear automatically after typing "use" and space. Or, can be forced up as usual with Ctrl+Space.

We also need to make sure that "namespace" suggestions do not appear in that scope.

I posted this request a while ago on StackOverflow here: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/9414781/aptana-simple-inline-conditionals-for-php 
